ft_printfsfsfsdfsadfsddsfdsds.manual_html:
ft_isblank

im med

Synopsis

int ft_isblank(int c);

Description

Returns non-zero if c is a blank character in the "C" locale. Recognized blanks are:

  • Space ' '
  • Horizontal tab '\t'

Return Value

1 if blank, 0 otherwise.

Notes

Use with values representable as unsigned char or EOF.

ft_queue_enqueue.manual_html:
ft_queue_enqueue

Adds an element to the rear of the queue.

Synopsis

bool ft_queue_enqueue(t_queue *queue, void *data);

Description

Appends data at the queue's rear in O(1). The queue does not own the memory pointed by data.

Return Value

true on success, false on failure (e.g., allocation error).

ft_isblank.name: ft_isblank
ft_isblank.description: Checks whether c is a blank character. In the C locale, blank characters are space (' ') and horizontal tab ('\t').
ft_isblank.return_value: Returns 1 if c is a blank character, 0 otherwise.

examples.title: Basic usage

notes: Behavior mirrors the standard isblank for the 'C' locale.
Argument must be representable as unsigned char or EOF.
ft_isblank.manual_html:
ft_isblank

im med

Synopsis

int ft_isblank(int c);

Description

Returns non-zero if c is a blank character in the "C" locale. Recognized blanks are:

  • Space ' '
  • Horizontal tab '\t'

Return Value

1 if blank, 0 otherwise.

Notes

Use with values representable as unsigned char or EOF.
